contact.name: Ms Yvonne Hg
contact.additionalNotes:
Delivers within 10km of the food bank location in Ipoh.; Called and spoke to Ms Yvonne on 22/07/2021 (Phone call lasted 30 minutes). This is a medium-sized NGO that has been running for 4 years by 4 ladies and 2 more volunteers. It will continue to operate after MCO ceases. Ms Yvonne is open to collaborate with local MP offices to pack and distribute supplies. 

Ms Yvonne comments that she's seeing the needy comprising of not only the older generation but also those who are of ages 30+ coming in for help.

Once the registration form is filled and they understand the background of the visitor, supplies are given out based on needs (number of mouths to feed) and recorded to ensure that people do not come in too frequently asking for supplies unless legit reasons are given.

Donations come from the public as far as people in Singapore (ie. they arrange delivery from Tesco) but they have a high level of traffic and frequent donations are highly needed.

The food bank is currently fixed at a location (rented the premise and has a refrigerator/freezer to keep supplies).

They have controls in place when it comes to giving out dry supplies/fresh food/necessities to avoid cases of people taking advantage of their supplies. However, Ms Yvonne is still open to trying the anti-cheating app.

Introduction :
The Zero Hunger Action - Love Angel Meals 零饥饿 "白旗求救行动" 爱心饭盒 Foodbank by Mama Vege Vegetarian/Vegan Restaurant started in April 2020. They are headquartered in Bukit Mertajam, Penang and is offering meals to those in need. They work with Padang Lalang N15 Women and Family Development Committee (Jawatankuasa Pembangunan Wanita dan Keluarga or "JPWK") (妇女及家庭发展委员会) to deliver meals to the needy.

HQ (Office & processing facilities) address: 20, Lorong Perda Timur 6, Bandar Perda, Bukit Mertajam 14000 Penang. 
Their restaurants in Malaysia are located at Bukit Mertajam (Penang), Sungai Petani  (Kedah), Ipoh (Perak) and PJ (Selangor).
---
Who are the recipients? :
(1) JWPK (NGO they are working with) will provide name lists of recipients in several locations to deliver meals to. (2) Those who are facing financial hardship or food shortage, or have friends or relatives facing difficulty can fill up this Google form to have food delivered to them: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScsxsH2CO1atr0Vv5oggjg2etbQISXGP_e94kM8CbA6FEi-XQ/viewform when they deliver the food to them for the first time, they will contact the recipients to get a further understanding of whether they need daily deliveries or other supplies. (3) MamaVege also supply meals to front-liners, RELA, police, old folks homes, children homes, OKU centres, poverty-stricken communities, etc.
---
What is being supplied? :
(1) Their main supply is the delivery of vegetarian meals (for lunch). There are roughly 1000+ meals supplied daily. (2) They also deliver groceries to other states using courier services.  
---
How is the delivery done?
Delivery is a combined effort between (1) MamaVege volunteers/staff (2) volunteers/staff from local MP/ADUN offices and (3) vegetarian restaurants or caterers (for Muslim-friendly food) in other states. 
---
What areas do they cover? :
They are focused on doing daily deliveries in Bukit Mertajam (Penang), Butterworth (Penang) and Kulim (Kedah). As or further areas like Sungai Petani (Kedah), Alor Setar (Kedah) and Ipoh (Perak), they will do at least two deliveries per week. MamaVege HQ also will collaborate with their branches and other local vegetarian restaurants or caterers (for Muslim-friendly food) in other states to prepare meals. MamaVege HQ provides the finances while they prepare the food and does the deliveries on their behalf. Other states include Klang (Selangor), Johor and Malacca.
---
What donations do they accept? : 
(1) Members of the public can donate funds in the form of buying RM5 meals through their website: https://mamavege.com/Product.aspx?sq=fa485eb8-9e97-49f1-8c15-0f6a47bf6e7e or transferring the fund to their bank account.
(2) The MamaVege team also gives out dry goods, face masks and vegetables that the public has donated to the families in need. Please inform them beforehand.
---
Problems faced? : 
(1) Groceries are getting expensive than before, but MamaVege still remain RM5 donation and do bear the expensive costing. MamaVege hope to do their best to reduce human hunger.
---
